        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "wangdi",
          "email": "di.wang@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2013-10-09 02:56:07.000000000",
          "tz": -420
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "wangdi",
          "email": "di.wang@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2013-01-29 10:04:36.000000000",
          "tz": -480
        },
        "subject": "LU-2183 osp: cleanup osp-on-ost",
        "message": "LU-2183 osp: cleanup osp-on-ost\n\nWith new quota design and FIDonOST introduced, a new connection\nfrom OST/MDTn to MDT0 is required for sending quota and sequence\nRPCs. This connection was implemented by adding a new special\nosp device named osp-on-ost, which introduced complexity to osp\ncode, and many hacks of checking the osp device name in both\nclient and server side code.\n\nIn this patch, we removed the osp-on-ost, and introduced a new\ndevice type lwp (Light Weight Proxy) to manage the light weight\nconnection established from OSTs/MDTs to MDT0.\n\nSigned-off-by: Niu Yawei <niu@whamcloud.com>\nSigned-off-by: Wang Di <di.wang@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: Ic1ba25f941a4f971a542dc4be8a81e28ee0f477b\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
